As his reputation grew from his time at Manchester United, Ronaldo has signed many sponsorship deals for consumer products, including sportswear, football boots (since November 2012 Ronaldo has worn the Nike Mercurial Vapor personalized CR7 edition),[450] soft drinks, clothing, automotive lubricants, financial services, electronics, and computer video games.[451][452][453][454] Ronaldo was featured as the cover athlete of EA Sports' FIFA video game FIFA 18 and was heavily involved in the game's promotion.[455] His 'Siiii' goal celebration features in the FIFA series, accompanied with his own voiceover.[430] He was also the face of Pro Evolution Soccer, appearing on the cover in 2008, 2012, and 2013.[456]
